properties.headline: Coastal Flood Advisory issued December 31 at 9:43PM EST until January 1 at 4:00AM EST by NWS Mount Holly NJ
properties.description:
* WHAT...Up to one half foot of inundation above ground level
expected in low-lying areas near shorelines and tidal
waterways.

* WHERE...Kent County in Maryland.

* WHEN...Until 4 AM EST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Flooding is possible in and near Rock Hall, Skinners
Neck, Piney Neck, McKinleyville, Cliffs City, and Chestertown.
properties.instruction:
If travel is required, allow extra time as some roads may be
closed. Do not drive around barricades or through water of
unknown depth. Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone
property.

NWSheadline: COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 AM EST WEDNESDAY
